<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Minimum and maximum widths with percentage based values</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#min-max-widths" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify percentage is calculated in relation to the containing block." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                width: 300px;
                height: 110px;
                background-color: blue;
                color: Blue;
            }
            #d2
            {
                width: 300px;
                max-width: 50%;
                height: 100px;
                background-color: green;
                color: green;
            }
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
                padding: 0;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the blue box has twice the width as the green box.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2">Filler Text</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>